From: zchee <zchee@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: 2026-05-20
Subject: [PATCH] Zle: avoid FD_SET overflow EXC_GUARD on macOS 26 (Tahoe)

macOS 26 turned __darwin_check_fd_set_overflow() into a fatal EXC_GUARD
(Application Triggered Fault, namespc=18, reason_code=0x2) whenever
FD_SET(fd, ...) is called with fd >= FD_SETSIZE (1024). Previously this
function was a soft warning.

Tahoe inserts a `disclaimer` wrapper between /usr/bin/login and the
shell. That wrapper inherits a wide FD table from its parent without
setting FD_CLOEXEC on every descriptor, so the shell's controlling
terminal (SHTTY) can be assigned an FD >= 1024.

The crash reliably reproduces via the new (Feb 2025) terminal probe
introduced by Oliver Kiddle:

  setup_zshQszle -> query_terminal -> probe_terminal -> getbyte ->
  raw_getbyte -> select()/FD_SET(SHTTY, ...) -> EXC_GUARD

This is fatal at every interactive shell startup on Tahoe builds that:
  - rely on raw_getbyte's HAVE_SELECT fallback (when configure fails to
    define HAVE_POLL because <poll.h> guards POLLIN behind a feature-
    test macro not enabled by -std=c2x), and/or
  - statically link zsh/zselect and zsh/zpty (whose FD_SET use can be
    pulled into the hot path by -flto).

Fix: relocate SHTTY below FD_SETSIZE before zle's setup runs anything
that might select() on it. Also relocate `shout` if it was fdopen()'d
over SHTTY so subsequent writes hit the new descriptor.

This is a no-op on Linux and pre-Tahoe macOS (SHTTY is already low).

---
 Src/Zle/zle_main.c | 47 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 47 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Src/Zle/zle_main.c b/Src/Zle/zle_main.c
index 37d587d02..9a9d971cd 100644
--- a/Src/Zle/zle_main.c
+++ b/Src/Zle/zle_main.c
@@ -30,9 +30,16 @@
 #include "zle.mdh"
 #include "zle_main.pro"
 
+#include <fcntl.h>
+#include <unistd.h>
+#include <errno.h>
+
 #ifdef HAVE_POLL_H
 # include <poll.h>
 #endif
+#ifdef HAVE_SYS_SELECT_H
+# include <sys/select.h>
+#endif
 #if defined(HAVE_POLL) && !defined(POLLIN) && !defined(POLLNORM)
 # undef HAVE_POLL
 #endif
@@ -2259,6 +2266,46 @@ setup_(UNUSED(Module m))
     comprecursive = 0;
     rdstrs = NULL;
 
+    /*
+     * macOS 26 (Tahoe) hard-faults on FD_SET(fd, ...) when
+     * fd >= FD_SETSIZE. Relocate SHTTY (and shout) below FD_SETSIZE
+     * before query_terminal() runs probe_terminal() -> getbyte()
+     * which may select() on SHTTY.
+     *
+     * No-op when SHTTY is already low or FD_SETSIZE is undefined.
+     */
+#ifdef FD_SETSIZE
+    if (SHTTY >= 0 && SHTTY >= FD_SETSIZE) {
+	int low_fd;
+# ifdef F_DUPFD_CLOEXEC
+	low_fd = fcntl(SHTTY, F_DUPFD_CLOEXEC, 3);
+# else
+	low_fd = fcntl(SHTTY, F_DUPFD, 3);
+	if (low_fd >= 0)
+	    (void) fcntl(low_fd, F_SETFD, FD_CLOEXEC);
+# endif
+	if (low_fd >= 0 && low_fd < FD_SETSIZE) {
+	    if (shout != NULL && fileno(shout) == SHTTY) {
+		FILE *new_shout = fdopen(low_fd, "w");
+		if (new_shout != NULL) {
+		    fflush(shout);
+		    fclose(shout);   /* closes the old high SHTTY */
+		    shout = new_shout;
+		    SHTTY = low_fd;
+		} else {
+		    /* could not rewrap shout; back out */
+		    close(low_fd);
+		}
+	    } else {
+		close(SHTTY);
+		SHTTY = low_fd;
+	    }
+	} else if (low_fd >= 0) {
+	    close(low_fd);   /* dup landed high again; give up safely */
+	}
+    }
+#endif /* FD_SETSIZE */
+
     /* detect terminal color and features */
     if (shout)
 	query_terminal();
